NAME
    Plack::Middleware::Debug::Mongo - Extend Plack::Middleware::Debug with
    MongoDB panels

VERSION
    version 0.01

SYNOPSIS
        # inside your psgi app
        use Plack::Builder;

        my $app = sub {[
            200,
            [ 'Content-Type' => 'text/html' ],
            [ '<html><body>OK</body></html>' ]
        ]};

        my $options = { host => 'mongodb://mongo.example.com:29111' };

        builder {
            mount '/' => builder {
                enable 'Debug',
                    panels => [
                        [ 'Mongo::ServerStatus', connection => $options ],
                    ];
                $app;
            };
        };

DESCRIPTION
    This distribution extends Plack::Middleware::Debug with some MongoDB
    panels. At the moment, panels listed below are available.

PANELS
  Mongo::ServerStatus
    Display panel with generic MongoDB server information which is available
    by the command *db.serverStatus()*. See
    Plack::Middleware::Debug::Mongo::ServerStatus for additional
    information.

BUGS
    Please report any bugs or feature requests through the web interface at
    <https://github.com/Wu-Wu/Plack-Middleware-Debug-Mongo/issues>

